\id OBA - Wycliffe’s Bible Modern Spelling Enhanced, Word Files Text Conversion and standardization, E. Boot 05 2019
\h OBADIAH
\toc1 OBADIAH
\toc2 Obadiah
\toc3 OBA
\mt1 OBADIAH
\c 1
\p 
\v 1 \add [The]\add* Vision of Obadiah. The Lord God saith these things to Edom. We heard an hearing of the Lord, and he sent a legate, \em either a messenger\em*, to heathen men. Rise ye, and together rise we against him into battle. \sls (The vision, \em or the prophecy\em*, of Obadiah. The Lord God saith these things about Edom. We heard a word from the Lord, and he sent a messenger to the heathen. And he said, Rise ye, let us rise up together against Edom in battle.)\sls*
\p 
\v 2 Lo! I gave thee \sls (to be)\sls* little in heathen men, thou art full much worthy to be despised. \sls (Behold! I made thee, \em (O Edom)\em*, to be the least among the heathen, and thou art very worthy to be despised.)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 The pride of thine heart enhanced thee, dwelling in the crazings of stones, araising thy seat. Which sayest in thine heart, Who shall draw me down into earth? \sls (The pride of thy heart exalted thee, \em or raised thee up\em*, thou living in the chinks of stones, and making thy home high in the heights. Who sayest in thy heart, Who can ever pull me down to the ground?)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 Though thou shalt be raised as an eagle, and thou shalt put thy nest among stars, from thence I shall draw thee down, saith the Lord. \sls (But even though thou shalt be raised up like an eagle, and \em even if\em* thou shalt put thy nest among the stars, I shall \em still\em* pull thee down from there, saith the Lord.)\sls*
\p 
\v 5 If night thieves had entered to thee, if outlaws by night, how shouldest thou have been still? whether they should not have stolen things enough to them? If gatherers of grapes had entered to thee, whether they should have left namely raisins, \em or clusters\em*, to thee? \sls (If night thieves come in upon thee, yea, outlaws by night, do they not steal only what they want for themselves? And if gatherers of grapes come in upon thee, do they not at least leave the raisins, \em (or the clusters)\em*, for thee? But thy enemies have left thee with nothing!)\sls*
\p 
\v 6 How sought they Esau, searched the hid things of him? \sls (Yea, how they sought out Esau, and searched for all his hidden treasures, \em (or all his riches)\em*!)\sls*
\p 
\v 7 Till to the terms they sent out thee; and all men of thy covenant of peace scorned, \em either deceived\em*, thee, men of thy peace waxed strong against thee; they that shall eat with thee, shall set ambush, \em either treasons\em*, under thee; \sls (and they shall say)\sls*, there is no prudence \sls (left)\sls* in him. \sls (And they sent thee out unto thy borders; and all thy allies mocked, \em or deceived\em*, thee, yea, men at peace with thee grew strong against thee; those who ate with thee, set ambush for thee; and they said, There is no wisdom left in him.)\sls*
\p 
\v 8 Whether not in that day, saith the Lord, I shall lose the wise men of Idumea, and prudence \sls (out)\sls* of the mount of Esau? \sls (On that day, saith the Lord, I shall destroy the wise men of Edom, and leave no wisdom on the mount of Esau!)\sls*
\p 
\v 9 And thy strong men shall dread of midday, \em either south\em*, that a man of the hill of Esau perish. \sls (And thy strong men, O Teman, shall have fear, and everyone on the mount of Esau shall perish.)\sls*
\p 
\v 10 For slaying and for wickedness against thy brother Jacob, confusion shall cover thee, and thou shalt perish \add [into]\add* without end. \sls (For the killing and the wickedness done against thy brother Jacob, shame shall cover thee, and thou shalt be cut off forever.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 In the day when thou stoodest against him, when aliens took the host of him, and strangers entered into the gates of him, and sent lot on Jerusalem, thou were also as one of them. \sls (For on the day when thou stoodest aside, and when foreigners took all of his wealth, and strangers entered into his gates, and cast lots for Jerusalem, thou were just like one of them.)\sls*
\p 
\v 12 And thou shalt not despise in the day of thy brother, in the day of his pilgrimage, and thou shalt not be glad on the sons of Judah, in the day of perdition of them; and thou shalt not magnify thy mouth in the day of anguish, \sls (And thou should not have had glory on the day of thy brother, on the day of his misfortune, and thou should not have been happy over the sons of Judah, on the day of their perdition; and thou should not have opened thy mouth \em in laughter, and mocking\em*, on the day of their anguish,)\sls*
\p 
\v 13 neither thou shalt enter into the gate\sls (s)\sls* of my people, in the day of falling of them; and thou shalt not despise in the evils of him, in the day of his destroying; and thou shalt not be sent out against his host, in the day of his destroying; \sls (nor should thou have entered into the gates of my people, on the day of their falling; and thou should not have seized their treasures, \em or their riches\em*, on the day of their destruction; and thou should not have gone out against their host, \em or their army\em*, on the day of their destruction;)\sls*
\p 
\v 14 neither thou shalt stand in the going out \add [of the ways]\add*, that thou slay them that fled; and thou shalt not close together the residues, \em either left men\em*, of him, in the day of tribulation, \sls (nor should thou have stood in the going out of the ways, so that thou could kill those who fled; and thou should not have enclosed their remnants, \em or those who were left\em*, on the day of their tribulation,)\sls*
\p 
\v 15 for the day of the Lord is nigh on all heathen men. As thou hast done, it shall be done to thee; he shall convert thy yielding into thine head. \sls (for the day of the Lord is near for all the heathen. As thou hast done, now it shall be done to thee; and what thou hast yielded, shall now return upon thy own head.)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 For as ye drank on mine holy hill, all heathen men shall drink busily, and they shall drink, and they shall swallow up; and they shall be as if they be not. \sls (For as ye drank on my holy hill, all the heathen shall busily drink, and they shall drink, and they shall swallow it all down; and then they shall be as if they had never been.)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 And salvation shall be in the hill of Zion, and it shall be holy; and the house of Jacob shall wield them which wielded them. \sls (And deliverance shall be upon Mount Zion or And those who escape shall be upon Mount Zion, and it shall be holy; and the house of Jacob shall rule those who once ruled them.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 And the house of Jacob shall be fire, and the house of Joseph \em shall be\em* flame, and the house of Esau \em shall be\em* stubble; and they shall be kindled in them, and they shall devour them; and remnants shall not be of the house of Esau, for the Lord spake, \sls (or and no one of the house of Esau shall be left, for the Lord hath spoken)\sls*.
\p 
\v 19 And these that be at the south, shall inherit the hill of Esau; and they that be in the low fields, \em shall inherit\em* Philistines; and they shall wield the country of Ephraim, and the country of Samaria; and Benjamin shall wield Gilead. \sls (And then those who be at the south, \em or in the Negeb\em*, shall inherit the mount of Esau; and those who be in the low lands, \em or in the Shephelah, shall inherit\em* the Philistines; and they shall possess the countryside of Ephraim, and the countryside of Samaria; and Benjamin shall possess Gilead.)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 And transmigration, \em either passing over\em*, of this host of sons of Israel \em shall wield\em* all places of Canaanites, till to Zarephath; and the transmigration of Jerusalem, which is in Sepharad, shall wield the cities of the south. \sls (And this army of the exiles of the Israelites \em shall possess\em* all the places of the Canaanites, unto Zarephath; and the exiles of Jerusalem, who be in Sardis, shall possess the cities of the south, \em or of the Negeb\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 And saviours shall go up into the hill of Zion, for to deem the hill of Esau, and a realm shall be to the Lord. \sls (And the victors shall go up from Mount Zion, to judge the mount of Esau, and the kingdom shall be the Lord’s.)\sls* 
